    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Pura - Women Empowerment</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Ankit Mahto, Ankit Srivastava</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Pura<br />Women Empoerment</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2011 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5072</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Even after so many years of Indian independence and becoming a republic , it’s still very sad to see that a major part of the country are still forbidden from the basic amenities that the higher, so to say the upper class of the society enjoy.
This project is just a small help in providing a few facilities to those rural people of the country. This PURA project is basically the idea of our former president of India, Honourable Dr A.P.J. Abdul Kalam, who sought of this idea.
In this project we aim at providing Women Empowerment, as a part of the PURA project to the people of Kancheepuram District of Tamil Nadu.
Women Empowerment is meant for creating and building relationships to a wonderful and important end: to level the playing field so that we can unleash all the talent in these crucial disciplines and enables it to flourish.
The empowerment of women by SHGs (Self Help Groups) has been instituted in Tamilnadu as early as in 1998 in Dharmapuri District. The success of this had led to outcome of Mahalir Thittam (Plan for Women) was launched from 1997-98. In 1992, NABARD (National Bank for Agricultural as good as Rural Development) conducted the commander project, as the partnership indication in in between SHGs, BANKS, as good as NGOs as good as found which it was some-more successful as good as effective .
Women Empowerment is meant for creating and building relationships to a wonderful and important end: to level the playing field so that we can unleash all the talent in these crucial disciplines and enables it to flourish.
Women empowerment takes place in the fields of Economics, Education, Social, Cultural, and Psychology as good as Politics. It represents Economic Independence, Self-reliant, Self-confidence, Leadership, Respect, Recognition, Political, Social as good as authorised awareness. SHG promotes thrift, savings, and entrepreneurship skills upon top of changing the amicable perspective as good as standing of women in society. Micro financial activities have been mercantile activities in building empowerment of women. SHGs have been not usually the micro-credit groups though additionally the amicable certainty groups. The United Nations’ third Millennium Goal is, to foster Gender Equality as well as Women Empowerment.</td></tr>
